beer.beer_description: We used our one-of-a-kind Hop Torpedo to deliver an intense rush of hop flavor and the lush aromas of mango, papaya, and passionfruit with every sip.  Enjoy our tropical twist on the American IPA. This beer is hopped with Amarillo, Citra, Comet, El Dorado, and Mosaic
This is our house Belgian. This 7.7% Belgian Blonde is dry, highly carbonated and very easy to drink. Tons of banana and bubble gum in the aroma. This beer makes people fall down!

This beer has a pop of bright orange flavor that emphasizes the natural citrus-heavy character of Cascade, Equinox and Mandarina hops. Brewed with orange peel added directly to the kettle, and all the classic hop flavor you'd come to expect from our all-new take on the hop-forward fruit beer.

With deep black color, a thick, creamy head, rich chocolate, toffee and coffee flavors, and full-bodied smoothness, Anchor PorterÂ® is the epitome of a handcrafted dark beer.

A blend of specially roasted pale, caramel, chocolate, and black malts, along with our top-fermenting yeast, creates complexity without bitterness. The brew is hopped at a high rate, and naturally carbonated. The result is dark in the glass, but surprisingly light on the palate.

Anchor PorterÂ® became the first modern American porter when it was introduced in 1972. As we celebrate its 40th anniversary, our porter continues to reward those who look beyond its intimidating appearance to discover its smooth, full-bodied drinkability. Anchor PorterÂ® is the definitive American Porter.

A full-bodied brown ale with smooth hints of pumpkin and brown sugar. We brew our Punkin Ale with pumpkin meat, brown sugar and spices. As the season cools, this is the perfect beer to warm up with.
Punkin Ale is named after the seriously off-centered southern Delaware extravaganza Punkin Chunkin (check out some of these Discovery Channel videos of Punkin Chunkin, you gotta see it to believe it!). In fact, Punkin Ale made its debut as it claimed first prize in the 1994 Punkin Chunkin Recipe Contest. Yes, that was a full 6 months before we even opened our doors for business!

Adobe Igloo is our New Mexican answer to the classic Winter Warmer: dark red, full-bodied, and malt-forward. Traditionally, Winter Warmers are balanced with extra hops or a Wintery spice blend. We instead drew on our rich culinary heritage and focused on cacao nibs and red chile flakes. Offering chile flavor without heat and dusty raw cocoa rather than sweet chocolate, Adobe Iglooâ€™s intriguing complexity will keep you coming back, sip after warming sip.

Inside every dog, thereâ€™s a TurbodogÂ® ready to break free. This brown ale has a rich, dark color and body with a sweet chocolate, toffee-like flavor. TurbodogÂ® is powered by
pale, caramel and chocolate malts and Willamette hops for runaway good times.

An India Pale Ale brewed with a generous amount of rye malt, this beer pours a deep orange, ruby red color reminiscent of the world famous Haleakala Crater sunrises it was inspired by. Medium bodied with a strong spicy, herbal character from both the use of rye malt and Chinook and Zythos hops. Rounded out with a touch of caramel sweetness and a pleasant bitter finish.

NEW LOOK - SAME WORLD CLASS LIQUID

This ale is brewed with passion fruit, orange and guava the beer will paddle in at 4.5%-AbV.
Brilliantly balanced for easy drinking, this pale ale is packed with citrus and tropical fruit flavors from eight different hop varieties.

Brewed as an ode to everyone's favorite frozen treat. Popcycle Blonde ale takes raspberries and lemons and combines them for a poolside sipper. This beer evokes the sound of the ice cream truck approaching. Popcycle Blonde is light, sweet, and thirst quenching made for hot days and good times.
Four types of West Coast hops add bold notes of pine and juicy grapefruit to this deep golden wheat ale, for a crisp flavor thatâ€™s a refreshing escape from winterâ€™s lingering chill.
Named for the Haitian god of agriculture, Azacca IPA boasts citrus, mango and orchard fruit notes on a sweet Caramel malt backbone.

Parched motorists on Route 66 anticipated hospitality at Tower Station, opened in 1936. This unfiltered India Pale Ale greets you with a copper-orange hue and fluffy white head, releasing aromas of tangerine and pineapple. Pilsner and Pale malts balance hop derived flavors of grapefruit peel and pine to finish the journey.

Hop Heads unite! This West Coast style IPA feeds the hops fiends that clamor for the greenery. Mango, melon and fresh cut pine fills the air and you are taken to your refuge! Chinook, Simcoe, Cascade and Columbus are all to blame for your love of our take on the IPA. Let this be your refuge of taste!

A Belgian wit (white) beer brewed with white and black peppercorns and experimental hop HBC 291. The black and white peppercorns enhance the peppery character produced by the wit yeast, and the hops round out the aroma with citrus and dark fruit character.

SanTan Brewing 
has partnered with the Arizona Coyotes to create Yotes Pale Ale. 

The color of this American Pale Ale is Coyotes brick red created by the use of natural Hibiscus flowers.  

YPA has an ABV of 
5.4% and 40 IBU 
and was created using flavorful Cascade, Nelson Sauvin and Citra hops.

AZ Farmhouse is a beer we brewed for the preparation of the upcoming heat.  Traditionally brewed for the Belgian farmworkers to drink during the hot summer months, we too felt that a Saison, or Farmhouse Ale, would help make the impending summer much more bearable.  Our Farmhouse Ale has notes of tropical fruit and berries, balanced by a slight clove spice and hop bitterness.  You need not be a farm worker to really enjoy this beer.

Well, looks like grandma has gone nuts. This English style brown ale hits you upside the head with a nose chock-full of toasted Georgia pecan flavors followed by a rich, full-bodied finish. Just like grandmaâ€™s pecan pie, this baby will have you coming back for more. So, what are you waiting for? Pop the top and give old grandma a kiss.

This dark amber wheat beer features fruity and spicy aromas galore.  Significant strength underlies the pleasant citric appeal of this bock beer. Redolent with the flavors of harvest fruit, Moonglow typifies the traditional weizenbock-style so thoroughly enjoyed throughout Bavaria. Left unfiltered, its unique yeast strain gives Moonglow a radiance all its own.

Miller High Life, also known as the Champagne of Beers, is a quintessentially classic, American-style lager. To this day, Miller High Life continues to be faithfully brewed as a golden pilsner, utilizing light-stable galena hops from the Pacific Northwest and a select combination of malted barley.

Named after the ethereal song by the one and only Deftones, Phantom Bride IPA is a blend of Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, and Mosaic hops delicately balanced for the perfectly drinkable mix of citrus and hoppy goodness.

This seasonal beer is a limited edition brewed for the short days and long nights of winter. The Brown Ale style originated in the pubs of England, where beer drinkers desired a beer that was both flavorful and complex, but at the same time mild enough to be a session beer. The Santa Fe Brewing Company's interpretation of this style uses a combination of high mash temperature, hard water, and low-alpha acid hops to produce a product that is both true to the style and distinctly Santa Fe. Brewing jargon aside, Santa Fe Nut Brown Ale is an easy-drinking beer, mild, smooth, and always a favorite. Try a keg at your next party!

Looking for something other than pumpkin beers? This was our 
answer, a big and bold flavored maple beer. Finally a beer you
can enjoy in the fall and in the morning. This beer has been 
known to pair very well with waffles and pancakes. Drink it
with your breakfast or pour it on top.

A robust American spiced porter brewed with vanilla beans, brown rice syrup, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Classic holiday spice notes are prevalent while chocolate, coffee and dark fruit linger with a smooth finish. Weighs in at 5.1% for your holiday enjoyment!

This delicately balanced Strong Ale starts with dark copper color mixed with slight reddish hues and a light tan head. Big malty aroma with a Munich character give way to a slight caramel & toffee mixed with spicy noble hop aroma, all wrapped together with a medium-bodied mouth feel. German malt flavor profile with slight roasty notes give Pray for Snow a subtle toffee sweetness balanced with spicy hop bitterness and slight alcohol warming. Served appropriately in a classic snifter.
Bohemia Clasica is a pale Mexican lager that has become a popular choice for beer drinkers looking for a brew that is readily available and affordable.
